Quick start
===========

1. Get a copy of sci2web from https://github.com/facom/Sci2Web:

   NOTE: You can get an anonymous clone of the project using:

      git clone git://github.com/facom/Sci2Web.git

   Then you will be able to get updates using 'git pull'.

2. Place it in a web-available directory at your server
   (e.g. /var/www/<directory>)

3. Read the installation guide at
   http://localhost/<directory>/sci2web/doc/install.html

For the contirbutor
===================

1. Generate a public key of your account at the server where you will
   develop contributions:

   $ ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "user@email"

2. Upload public key to the github project site
   (https://github.com/facom/Sci2Web).  You will need access to the
   account where the repository was created.

3. Configure git:

   $ git configure --global user.name "Your Name"
   $ git configure --global user.email "your@email"

4. Get an authorized clone of the master trunk:

   $ git clone git@github.com:facom/Sci2Web.git

